REST API header
In this module I set the default:
All-Content = True

Without it the following occurs:

6.100.1. get GET
Get details of a brick.
Retrieves status details of brick from underlying gluster volume with header All-Content set to true.
This is the equivalent of running gluster volume status <volumename> <brickname> detail.

7.122.6. network_operation_in_progress
Specifies whether a network-related operation, such as 'setup networks', 'sync networks', or 'refresh capabilities', is currently being executed on this host.
The header All-Content:true must be added to the request in order for this attribute to be included in the response.

7.142.4. initialization
Reference to the virtual machine’s initialization configuration.
Since oVirt 4.1.8 this property can be cleared by sending an empty tag.
The response to such a request, and requests with the header All-Content: true will still contain this attribute.

7.142.13. tpm_enabled
If true, a TPM device is added to the virtual machine. By default the value is false. This property is only visible when fetching if "All-Content=true" header is set.

I included a -Syncopate switch option on all the Get-XXXX functions to remove it and only return a truncated property set. This vastly improves performance when the additional data is not required

when you use the -syncopate switch on Get-oVM, the $oVM.initialization.configuration is not returned
which we use to determine the PCI bus slot allocations
([XML]$oVM.initialization.configuration.data).Envelope.Content.Section.Where({$_.type -eq "ovf:VirtualHardwareSection_Type"}).ChildNodes.Where({$_.address}) | Select Type, Device, Address | Sort Address
