		.PARAMETER EnablePowerManagement
			Indicates whether power management configuration is enabled or disabled.
		.PARAMETER KdumpIntegration
			Toggles whether to determine if kdump is running on the host before it is shut down. 
			When set to true, the host will not shut down during a kdump process. 
			This is set to true when a host has power management enabled, unless disabled by the user.
		.PARAMETER DisablePolicyControlOfPowerManagement
			Disable policy control of power management
			Toggles the automated power control of the host in order to save energy. 
			When set to true, the host will be automatically powered down if the cluster’s load is low, 
			and powered on again when required. This is set to true when a host is created, unless disabled by the user.
		.PARAMETER KSMEnabled (Not working ???)
			Kernel SamePage Merging (KSM) reduces references to memory pages from multiple identical pages to a 
			single page reference. Memory Deduplication. Boolean to Enable/Disable
			
			This property might be read only, AND triggers only when enabled on the cluster AND when the oHost 
			is under memory pressure
		.PARAMETER TransparentHugePageEnabled (Not working ???)
			Transparent huge page support expands the size of memory pages beyond the standard 4 KiB limit.
			Enable and set huge pages configuration. Boolean to Enable/Disable 
		.PARAMETER UpgradeCheck
			Switch to Check if there are VDSM and selected software upgrades available for the host.
		.PARAMETER Upgrade
			Switch to Upgrade VDSM and selected software upgrades available for the host.
		.PARAMETER SkipUpgradeReboot
			Switch to Skip the host reboot after the upgrade. By default the host is rebooted.
		.PARAMETER EnrollCertificate
			Switch to Enroll the certificate of the host.
			Useful in case you get a warning that it is about to expire or has already expired.
		.PARAMETER Refresh
			Switch to Refresh the host devices and capabilities.
		.PARAMETER FencePowerStatus
			Switch to retrieve the power status of the oHost via the Fence Agent
		.PARAMETER FenceAgentAction
			Add a new fencing-agent to the oHost, or Remove or Reorder Existing fencing-agent(S)
			Valid Options "add","remove","reorder"
		.PARAMETER FenceAgentType
			Select Type/Model to add a new Fencing Agent
			Valid Options "apc","apc_snmp","bladecenter","cisco_ucs","drac5","drac7","eps","hpblade","ilo","ilo2","ilo3","ilo4","ilo_ssh","ipmilan","redfish","rsa","rsb","wti"
		.PARAMETER FenceAgentOrder
