Function New-oAffinityGroup{
	<#
		.SYNOPSIS
			This function creates a new oAffinityGroup on an oCluster, on an oVirt Server system.
		.DESCRIPTION
			This function creates a new oAffinityGroup on an oCluster, on an oVirt Server system.
		.PARAMETER Name
			The Name of the new oAffinityGroup on an oCluster, on an oVirt Server system.
		.PARAMETER Description
			A human-readable description in plain text.
		.PARAMETER oCluster
			The oCluster target to create the new oAffinityGroup
			Can be a text name or an [oCluster] PSObject
		.PARAMETER oClusterId
			The oCluster target Id to create the new oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oClusterUid
			The oCluster target Uid to create the new oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oHost
			The oHost(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
			Can be a text name(s) or an [oHost] PSObject(s)
		.PARAMETER oHostId
			The oHost Id(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oHostUid
			The oHost Uid(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oHostLabel
			The oHostLabel(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
			Can be a text name(s) or an [oHostLabel] or [oAffinityLabel] PSObject(s)
		.PARAMETER oHostLabelId
			The oHostLabel Id(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oHostLabelUid
			The oHostLabel Uid(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oVM
			The oVM(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
			Can be a text name(s) or an [oVM] PSObject(s)
		.PARAMETER oVMId
			The oVM Id(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oVMUid
			The oVM Uid(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oVMLabel
			The oVMLabel(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
			Can be a text name(s) or an [oVMLabel] or [oAffinityLabel] PSObject(s)
		.PARAMETER oVMLabelId
			The oVMLabel Id(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER oVMLabelUid
			The oVMLabel Uid(s) to add to the created oAffinityGroup
		.PARAMETER Priority
			Priority determines which affinity groups are broken if it’s not possible to maintain all of them when starting or migrating a VM. 
			Affinity groups with lower priority are more likely to be broken.
			Decimal number
		.PARAMETER HostAffinityRule (Disabled, Positive, Negative)
			oHost Polarity
			Specifies whether the affinity group applies positive affinity or negative affinity to KVM hosts that are members of that affinity group.
